---
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro'
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---
<Layout title="AI Visibility Case Study | Rank4AI" description="How a UK professional services business built AI search visibility from the ground up. Audit findings, strategy, and outcomes.">
<section class="pt-12 pb-24 reveal">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Research', href: '/research/' },
      { label: 'Case Studies', href: '/research/case-studies/' },
      { label: 'Ai Visibility' }
    ]} />

    <p class="section-tag">Case Study</p>
    <h1 class="mb-6">AI Visibility Case Study</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-text-muted mb-8">UK Professional Services · 2026</p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 mb-4">The Challenge</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">A UK professional services business with a strong Google presence was completely absent from AI search answers. Despite ranking on page one for their target keywords, ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini and Perplexity did not mention them when asked about businesses in their category.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">The Audit</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Our AI Search Visibility Audit revealed gaps across all five signal layers:</p>
    <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Identity Clarity</span> – described differently across website, LinkedIn, and directory listings</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Subject Authority</span> – services listed broadly with no structured depth content</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Meaning Architecture</span> – no schema markup, poor internal linking hierarchy</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Ecosystem Validation</span> – present on only 3 external platforms (website, GBP, LinkedIn)</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><p class="text-sm text-text-muted"><span class="highlight">Signal Consistency</span> – historical content contradicting current positioning</p></div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">The Approach</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">We started with the Google Ecosystem service – building presence across 20+ Google-owned platforms without touching the client's website. In parallel, we aligned external directories, review platforms, and professional listings to use consistent language.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">The Outcome</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Within 3 months, the business began appearing in AI-generated answers across multiple platforms. The consistent entity description built during the ecosystem phase gave AI systems the confidence to recommend the business.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The client described the experience: "We knew AI search was going to be a big shift. It felt important to understand this properly and build a solid baseline early on."</p>

    <div class="bg-off-white border border-border rounded-xl p-6 text-center mt-12">
      <p class="font-display text-xl text-teal">AI visibility is infrastructure, not a campaign.<br>It compounds.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="bg-off-white border-t border-border text-center py-16 px-10 mt-16">
    <h2 class="!text-2xl mb-4">Want similar results?</h2>
    <a href="/free-audit/" class="cta-primary">Get a Free AI Search Visibility Audit &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
